			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2011</a> paper:</span><br><i>Metacompiling OWL Ontologies</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AndersNilsson.html">Anders Nilsson</a>, <a href="../profile/GörelHedin.html">Görel Hedin</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_20">10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_20</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3e.html"><span class="tagM">T3E: Ontologies</span></a><ul><li> The paper directly targets OWL ontologies as the primary language artifact.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagL">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> ‘Metacompiling’ indicates a generative/compilation-style transformation from ontologies to executable artifacts.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3b.html"><span class="tagL">T3B: Transformation Languages</span></a><ul><li> The work centers on transformations over ontology descriptions to derive other representations.
</li></ul></li></ul>
